article.headline: Canisius 84, Rider 66
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Julius Coles scored a career-high 26 points to lead Canisius to their first Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference victory of the season, 84-66 over Rider, on Thursday night. Leading 50-45 with 15 minutes left in the second half, Canisius (6-11, 1-6 MAAC) used a 10-3 run to take command of the game. Coles capped the run with a 3-pointer, making the score 60-48 with 11:35 remaining. Rider (9-7, 4-2 MAAC) never pulled within six points the rest of the game. Frank Turner had 20 points for Canisius, eclipsing the 1,000-point plateau for his career. Greg Logins added 12 points. Ryan Thompson led Rider with 18 points, 14 in the second half. It was the most points Canisius has scored in a game this season. The Golden Griffins shot 50.4 percent from the floor, also a season best. Canisius snapped a four-game losing streak and a 12-game losing streak against the Broncs.
